<p>Step 1 of the "Build My First Site" exercise. Setting up your Sitecore environment.</p>
----field----
field: {5A5684BB-8B54-44F6-ABCC-2BADA05ADA5D}
name: Body
key: body
content-length: 2709

<p>Since you already have Sitecore installed, you can simply create another site in same instance.  We also need to finish setting up your machine for development.</p>
<h3>Adding A Site</h3>
<p>Sitecore easily supports multiple sites, and adding one only requires a few basic steps.</p>
<ol>
  <li>You need to create a root node for your new site.  In Launch Sitecore we have done this for you.  We called it Build My First Site Exercise.   </li>
  <li>You need to add a site node to the web.config file.  This has also been done for you using an external configuration file.  The file is /App_Config/Include/LaunchSitecore.config.  For more information about configuration files read this <a href="http://www.sitecore.net/Community/Technical-Blogs/John-West-Sitecore-Blog/Posts/2011/05/All-About-web-config-Include-Files-with-the-Sitecore-ASPNET-CMS.aspx" title="John West Blog" target="_blank">post</a> by John West. </li>
  <li>Add a binding to your IIS site called myfirstsite.launchsitecore </li>
  <li>Add an entry to you hosts file for 127.0.0.1 to match the binding.  The hosts file is located in \Windows\System32\drivers\etc </li>
</ol>
<p> </p>
<h3>Configuring Visual Studio</h3>
<p>The Launch Sitecore package you installed included a csproj file, so you can simply open it to view all of the code behind this site.  Once you do, Visual Studio will create a solution file for you. </p>
<p>For detailed steps on creating a Sitecore Visual Studio project for future Sitecore implementations, see John West's blog:  <a href="http://www.sitecore.net/community/technical-blogs/john-west-sitecore-blog/posts/2010/09/create-a-visual-studio-2010-project-for-a-sitecore-solution.aspx" title="Create a Visual Studio 2010 Project for a Sitecore Solution" target="_blank">Create a Visual Studio 2010 Project for a Sitecore Solution</a></p>
<h3>Installing Sitecore Rocks</h3>
<p>If you are using Visual Studio 2010, we have an extension called Sitecore Rocks which enhances the development experience.  We recommend that you install this now.  </p>
<p>In Visual Studio open Tools | Extension Manager and click the Online Gallery tab. In the search box, enter Sitecore Rocks and wait for Sitecore Rocks to appear. Click Download and follow the installation instructions.</p>
<p>Once it is installed you need to connect your project to your Sitecore server.  To do this right click on the project and click on Sitecore | Conenct.  This will open a dialog.  Please enter the appropriate values and click the OK button.  You will be prompted to install the advanced web service.</p>
